Why WestJet:
Every WestJet journey has the potential to enrich lives; a career with us is no exception.
WestJet arrived on the Canadian airline scene in 1996 and changed the industry for the better. We made air travel more affordable for Canadians and now we're going global.
Join us and love where you’re going.
Westjet is currently seeking a
Senior Administrative Assistant
to support the Finance organization. This dynamic multi-tasking individual is well organized, detail-oriented, proactive, flexible, and committed. A positive approach to building strong cross functional relationships is a must along with a passion for coordination and administration. The Senior Administrator will provide full support to the Vice President, Controller, Vice President, Financial Planning & Analysis and Vice President, Procurement & Supply Chain. This position deals with highly confidential information and requires the ability to exercise considerable discretion, judgement, and independent decision making. The work is high volume and fast-paced and deals with a broad spectrum of internal and external issues, stakeholders, and priorities.
Key Responsibilities:
Duties of this position encompass a broad range of tasks within the Finance organization. Some of the responsibilities will include, but will not be limited to:
Act as an ambassador to the VP’s offices, ensuring those engaging with it have a positive experience and works to positively influence the reputation of the VP’s offices for guests, WestJetters, and other stakeholders;
Provide the full scope of administrative support to VPs and general departmental support for the broader Finance organization;
Strategically manage the VPs calendars and schedules; managing correspondence, screening requests from internal and external parties; coordinating all meeting logistics including video conferencing, booking meeting rooms (internal & external venues), catering needs, and travel requirements as required;
Prepare, edit, and coordinate concise and consistent correspondence, communications and presentations for VPs;
Strong internal and external representative of finance policies and procedures leading by example; provide support to ensure best in class practices are used throughout organization;
Prepare and submit accurate expense reports, requisition and POs requests, invoice reconciliation and payment;
Maintain and organize digital and paper-based filing systems; ensures business reports, forms, and other documentation are readily available;
Manage Finance departments’ office supplies and spend to budget;
Assist with special projects as required; such as onboarding new employees, office space coordination, offsite meeting and event planning, etc.;
Brief VPs on relevant issues and provide both VPs with reliable and timely advice, support and liaison services, allowing him/her to focus on the delivery of WestJet strategic priorities and goals;
Collaborate with Executive Assistant to EVP, Finance and CFO and provide backup coverage as required;
Other administrative duties as needed to support the Finance Leadership Team and office of the CFO.
Experience and Qualifications:
Degree or diploma in Business Administration or related field;
Minimum 3 to 5 years’ administrative assistant experience, experience in accounting/finance environment is an asset;
Advanced knowledge and high proficiency in MS Office Suite (Outlook, Word, MS Teams, Excel, and Power Point) is required;
Experience in dealing with highly confidential information is required;
Very organized, strong attention to detail and superb time management skills; ability to maintain composure while managing multiple tasks in a fast paced environment;
Strong and highly flexible, proven interpersonal and communication skills, both written and verbal with proven experience dealing with confidential communications;
Must be able to prioritize and pivot fast and often, as the business needs dictate, without disruption to the tasks at hand;
Adaptable and able to take direction (sometimes little direction) and execute tasks in a timely manner;
Works well with all leadership styles and be a self-starter who requires minimal supervision.
The benefits of being a WestJetter:
WestJet provides all WestJetters with a competitive total rewards package. On top of that, we offer:
A fun and friendly culture with colleagues who work together to win
Travel privileges for you and your family, effective from your start date
Savings and Benefit programs that are flexible to meet your specific needs
Think we are a fit? Apply now!
About WestJet Group of Companies
Together with WestJet's regional airline, WestJet Encore, we offer scheduled service to more than 100 destinations in North America, Central America, the Caribbean and Europe and to more than 175 destinations in over 20 countries through our airline partnerships.
Our Safety Promise
At WestJet, the safety and security of our people and our guests is a core value and at the heart of what we do. As safety and security is a shared responsibility, it is expected that you will use safe work practices to ensure your well-being and the safety of others.
WestJet recognizes that the use of Alcohol and Drugs can adversely impact a safe work environment and the well-being of others including guests, suppliers and the public, as well as place WestJet's operations at risk. All roles that are identified as safety sensitive are required to pass a Pre-Employment Alcohol and Drug Test as per WestJet's Alcohol and Drug Policy.
As a federally regulated company, the WestJet group of companies is required to comply with all federal mandates. In order to be compliant with the recently-announced vaccination mandate, and to keep our guests/employees safe, all employees will be required to be fully vaccinated against Covid-19 as a condition of employment.
Our Commitment to Diversity and Inclusion
We embrace what makes us each unique, and what makes us uniquely WestJet. WestJet is committed to inclusiveness, equity, and accessibility and if you require accommodation during the selection process, please let our Talent Acquisition team know. We encourage all qualified candidates to apply. We thank all applicants for their interest in WestJet; however, only those candidates who are selected will be contacted.
For more information about everything WestJet, please visit WestJet.com.
